{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id5a27c561-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s202"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"202"},"text":"§ 202.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional finding and declaration of policy","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id5a27c562-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s202/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Congress finds that the existence, in industries engaged in commerce or in the production of goods for commerce, of labor conditions detrimental to the maintenance of the minimum standard of living necessary for health, efficiency, and general well-being of workers (1) causes commerce and the channels and instrumentalities of commerce to be used to spread and perpetuate such labor conditions among the workers of the several States; (2) burdens commerce and the free flow of goods in commerce; (3) constitutes an unfair method of competition in commerce; (4) leads to labor disputes burdening and obstructing commerce and the free flow of goods in commerce; and (5) interferes with the orderly and fair marketing of goods in commerce. That Congress further finds that the employment of persons in domestic service in households affects commerce.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id5a27c563-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s202/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" It is declared to be the policy of this chapter, through the exercise by Congress of its power to regulate commerce among the several States and with foreign nations, to correct and as rapidly as practicable to eliminate the conditions above referred to in such industries without substantially curtailing employment or earning power.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id5a27c564-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch676/s2"},"text":"June 25, 1938, ch. 676, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1060"},"text":"52 Stat. 1060","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-26/ch736/s2"},"text":"Oct. 26, 1949, ch. 736, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/910"},"text":"63 Stat. 910","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/259/s7/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–259, § 7(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-04-08"},"text":"Apr. 8, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/62"},"text":"88 Stat. 62","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id5a27c565-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5a27c566-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id5a27c567-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1974—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/259"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–259","children":[],"tail":" inserted finding of Congress that employment of persons in domestic service in households affects commerce."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1949—Subsec. (b). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-10-26"},"text":"Oct. 26, 1949","children":[],"tail":", inserted reference to regulation of commerce with foreign nations."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id5a27c568-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id5a27c569-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1974 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/259/s29/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–259, § 29(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-04-08"},"text":"Apr. 8, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/76"},"text":"88 Stat. 76","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/93/259/s29/a"},"text":"“Except as otherwise specifically provided, the amendments made by this Act [see Short Title of 1974 Amendment note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s201"},"text":"section 201 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall take effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-05-01"},"text":"May 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id5a27c56a-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1949 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-26/ch736/s16/a"},"text":"Act Oct. 26, 1949, ch. 736, § 16(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/919"},"text":"63 Stat. 919","children":[],"ta